  <summary>2/8/2006--Introduced.
Sergeant Henry Prendes Memorial Act of 2006 - Amends the federal criminal code to impose penalties for killing, or attempting or conspiring to kill, a current or former federally-funded public safety officer engaged in official duties or on account of the performance of official duties.</summary>
